Testing many SOS AM, last entry of day chronologically
Arrived on site and did startup meeting. Beginning to work through startup procedure
Opening aperture cover. Preparing for TAT alignment.
M1 cover opening for heat stop tests
M1 cover opening for heat stop tests
M2 moves for vignetting tests. Intermittent clouds.
Continued M2 moves for vignetting tests.
Various tests including ACS WCI, ViSP Polcal coordinated by HLS.
Plan of the day meeting completed, completed startup checklist.
Opening aperture cover, GOS and mirror cover.
CN working in Coudé for prep work. Blink tests for CN, opening, closing M1 at 10 sec, 30 sec, 1 min, 5 min increments. Using GOS Field Stop 2.8 and Field Stop 5'.
Prepping for GOS occulter tests, CN scan test.
CN context imager scan testing with 5' FOV GOS, running via CN controlled by Andre. Non redundant array and 5' Field Stop in GOS.
GOS 5' occulter thermal test. Limb tracker sensor testing while occulter in position.

GOS 5' occulter remains in position, moving in 45° steps around limb. Coordinating with CN and GOS teams to find the correct locations on limb for their testing (1.08 R☉). Few puffy clouds blowing through.
Moving CN to prominence, rotated Coudé angle so that the image is in the correct orientation on CN imager.
Noticed Enc Az velocity was zero, so checked Enc Az tab on the ECS and noticed motor fault. TechOps investigating.
Enc Az faulted again, but the mount is still taking radial positions so CN moving on with some testing while the Az is figured out. Enc Az fixed before it blocked the Sun so no lost time for CN.
CN tests ongoing. Using Field Stop 2.8' and 5'. Clouds passing over intermittently.
CN PolCal OP ran via OCS.
Closing M1 cover, moving to position to close aperture cover.
Opening sequence longer than usual because we were ready to go before the Sun was high enough to track. Waited for it to get to at least 8 degrees.
M9a moved into position for CN.
GOS 5' Occulter in CN testing on limb.
Attempted to move to Sun center, OCS/TCS did not take command. HLS fixed the issue.

CN test scans with various GOS positions (Air Force Target, Field Stop 2.8', Non Redundant Array), at various locations (filament, Sun center). Rotated Coudé angle from 0° to 90° HP mid way through this test period.
CN calibration tests starting at Coudé angle HP 90°, Sun center. Darks and gains being taken.
Coudé changed to AZEL reference frame, CN running observe tasks. Coudé changed back to HP reference frame, continuing CN observe tasks. Scattered high clouds blowing over.
Too many clouds passing over to continue testing.
partial opening procedure executed. Humidity is too high to open the M1 cover and the enclosure cover. Telescope and Enclosure tracking the center of the sun.
Cryo-NIRSP tests with the GOS lamp.
M9a moved to WCCS ready for boresight calibration.
Second part of the opening procedure completed. GOS setup for the execution of boresight calibration. Humidity ~ 73%.
Boresight calibration executed with some issues to adjust M3 position. The script is computing a M3 position out of range. Stacey investigating the issue.
M9a mirror moved back to Cryo-NIRSP.
procedure interrupted due to technical problem with the GOS. Bad health on the wheel hardware.
GOS technical problem. Full startup/shutdown troubleshooting procedure executed.
We executed boresight calibrations (pupil alignment and pinhole alignment). M9a mirror moved for Cryo-NIRSP and we started the tests for the day.
Enclosure Az axis stop tracking without any warning or error message. The problem was detected checking the TAT image (vignetting).

Cryo-NIRSP team executing some tests in the limb and 1.2 => 1.4 => 1.45 R⊙. We tried 1.5R⊙ but the command was rejected because out of the limits. We were requested to move Lyot stop but the commands are not working. Stephen was able to move the Lyot Stop remotely.
Executed two PolCal with Cryo from the OCS successfully. Experiment: sim-10-cn Obs. Program: sim-10-cn-polcal Obs. task: polcal IP name: sim-10 Pol Cal.
complete the tests for Cryo-NIRSP. No technical issues.
Waiting for IT&C walkthroughs and inspections.
Cryo-NIRSP calibrations and tests with the sun completed. Moving to Closed and Parked to continue tests with GOS Lamp.
Telescope closed and parked, but not shutting down. Continuing on to non-sun testing.
Continued Cryo-NIRSP GOS Lamp testing. Included testing via the Software team for GISS.
Clear skies, light wind. Nuria on HLS this morning, Hillary on assist and record-keeping. WFC having issues on startup. Luke and Erik on-summit, working on it.
Decide to start opening procedure while WFC team troubleshoots the startup of their system. Hillary works with Andy F. on startup of VBI Red while he sets up VBI Blue.
Troubleshooting issues at the cable wrap level. Seems to be a problem during opening sequence that the Enclosure is driving towards limit. Mount and Enclosure placed back in off position.
Small standby during the final part of opening procedure while WFC worked on fixing context viewer and VBI finished off dark calibrations.
Brief troubleshooting of PA&C flow during shutdown procedure. Luke and Erik will handle the shutdown of WFC later, not being handled by operators today.
FOCS Thermal Mode wouldn't switch to OnDisk. Stephen fixed the problem.
Erik going up to look at wavefront optics.

WCCS started to execute tests and calibrations. At the same time DL-NIRSP. We lost tracking for a minute with the ECS (az). No loss time, easy recovered without vignetting. DL-Nirsp continue with SAT.

We lost the mount while tracking, all axis went to OFF and the M1 cover was closed automatically. It seems to be that was kind of glitch in the power system. We recover the system doing a Reset of the axis, reset the GIS and back to tracking from the TCS.

Stephen executed limb finding tests for 10 minutes. DL-Nirsp OP to be executed but failed OP: sim-10-dlnirsp-polcal-f62. Logs showed script error, lack of information here for troubleshooting. Starting "manual" polcal sequence.
continue with DL-Nirsp SAT. Couple of tests for WCCS.
Stephen was testing the MCS altitude axis with a different acceleration setting.
Heat stop inspection. M1 thermal system pressure issues.
DL-NIRSP observing a pore at HG (long -52, lat 18), no solar rotation compensation, Coudé HP 0º (with an additional -91º "instrument" rotation angle.
07:20-07:27 Coudé interlock solved by 400V power restart Mount tracking Coudé off Enclosure active
Closing M1. Coudé off. Enclosure and Mount tracking.
Blink tests with Dark Shutter and Field Stop 2.8
Closing M1 due to particulates falling onto heat stop.
Falling particulates being investigated. DL-NIRSP calibrations continuing with GOS lamp instead of solar light.
Enclosure Aperture experienced a jerk movement at the beginning of closing procedure, so it was reopened and reclosed.
Closing M1, Coudé off. Enclosure and Mount tracking.
WFC off-limb scattering tests with Lyot stop at HPR (1.4, 0) Flats at the end at HP (0,0) circular motion.
DL-NIRSP off-disk observations at about HPR (1.1-1.2, 60º), (moving pointing around). Then Solar North: HPR (1.2, 0º)
DL-NIRSP testing back at sun center HP (0,0)
DL-NIRSP back at Solar North: HPR (1.2, 0º)
DL-NIRSP back at disk center HP (0, 0)
Trying to find a lockpoint for WFC around HPR (0.4, 136). Not successful.
DL-NIRSP tests on HPR (0.4, 136). WFC locking ocasionally. Not very good seeing.
